//Lateral meniscus degeneration - Classification - Grade 3

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
And I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select 'Lateral meniscus degeneration' from the Finding dropdown

When I select 'Grade 3' from Classification
Then 'Horizontal tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Longitudinal tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Radial tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Complex tear' radio button is enabled

And 'Superior articular surface' checkbox is enabled
And 'Inferior articular surface' checkbox is enabled

And 'Flap tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Bucket handle tear' radio button is enabled

When I click on 'Flap tear' radio button
Then 'Paratibial recess' radio button is enabled
And 'Parafemoral recess' radio button is enabled

When I click on 'Bucket handle tear' radio button
Then 'Double PCL sign' radio button is enabled
And 'Flipped meniscus sign' radio button is enabled
